  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarth\" title=\"House Tarth\"><img alt=\"House Tarth.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarth.svg/50px-House_Tarth.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarth.svg/75px-House_Tarth.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarth.svg/100px-House_Tarth.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Selwyn Tarth</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarth\" title=\"House Tarth\"><img alt=\"House Tarth.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarth.svg/50px-House_Tarth.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarth.svg/75px-House_Tarth.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarth.svg/100px-House_Tarth.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Selwyn_Tarth_by_Lu.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Selwyn Tarth by Lu.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/bc/Selwyn_Tarth_by_Lu.png/350px-Selwyn_Tarth_by_Lu.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"453\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/bc/Selwyn_Tarth_by_Lu.png/525px-Selwyn_Tarth_by_Lu.png 1.5x, /images/b/bc/Selwyn_Tarth_by_Lu.png 2x\" /></a><div>Selwyn Tarth, art by lupotterdraws ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nSelwyn of Tarth<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Evenstar\" title=\"Evenstar\">Evenstar</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Evenfall\" title=\"Lord of Evenfall\">Lord of Evenfall</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Tarth\" title=\"Lord of Tarth\">Lord of Tarth</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarth\" title=\"House Tarth\">House Tarth</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Stormlander\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Stormlander\">Stormlander</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_245_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">245&#160;AC</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_246_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">246&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafselwyn_tarth.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafselwyn_tarth.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\nDeceased wife<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Galladon_Tarth\" title=\"Galladon Tarth\">Galladon Tarth</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Tarth\" title=\"Alysanne Tarth\">Alysanne Tarth</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Tarth\" title=\"Arianne Tarth\">Arianne Tarth</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appendix)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Selwyn Tarth</b>, or <b>Selywn of Tarth</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Evenfall\" title=\"Lord of Evenfall\">Lord of Evenfall</a>, and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarth\" title=\"House Tarth\">House Tarth</a>, known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Evenstar\" title=\"Evenstar\">Evenstar</a>. Selwyn has one remaining child, his daughter and heir, <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafbrienne_tarth.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafbrienne_tarth.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Selwyn is said to be a good man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> He has large hands.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Selwyn's daughters <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Tarth\" title=\"Alysanne Tarth\">Alysanne</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Tarth\" title=\"Arianne Tarth\">Arianne</a> died in infancy. His son <a href=\"/index.php/Galladon_Tarth\" title=\"Galladon Tarth\">Galladon</a> drowned when he was eight years old, leaving Brienne as his only living child.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>After the death of his wife, Selwyn took a new <a href=\"/index.php/Mistress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress\">mistress</a> every year. One mistress came from across the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>; she had a slim waist, <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_eyes\" title=\"Purple eyes\">purple eyes</a>, and a lovely voice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Tarth had a <a href=\"/index.php/Septa\" title=\"Septa\">septa</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Roelle\" title=\"Roelle\">Roelle</a>, who educated Brienne. He also allowed his <a href=\"/index.php/Master-at-arms\" title=\"Master-at-arms\">master-at-arms</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Goodwin\" title=\"Goodwin\">Goodwin</a>, to train Brienne at arms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> He kept a singer every year of Brienne's childhood, which led her to memorize all the songs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Selwyn <a href=\"/index.php/Betrothed\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Betrothed\">betrothed</a> Brienne to the second son of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Bryen_Caron\" title=\"Bryen Caron\">Bryen Caron</a>, but the boy died of a <a href=\"/index.php/Disease\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Disease\">chill</a> when he was twelve.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Selwyn then tried to wed Brienne to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ronnet_Connington\" title=\"Ronnet Connington\">Ronnet Connington</a>, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> rejected her for her appearance.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> He last tried an older man for her, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Humfrey_Wagstaff\" title=\"Humfrey Wagstaff\">Humfrey Wagstaff</a>, but Brienne broke her betrothal to Wagstaff by defeating him in combat. After that, Lord Selwyn stopped trying to arrange a marriage for Brienne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Selwyn hosted <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Evenfall_Hall\" title=\"Evenfall Hall\">Evenfall Hall</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Paramount_of_the_Stormlands\" title=\"Lord Paramount of the Stormlands\">Lord Paramount of the Stormlands</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_age\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coming of age\">coming of age</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Progress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Progress\">progress</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> Some time later, Selywn sent Brienne to serve Renly at <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> is sent to ask after the allegiance of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlords\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Stormlords\">stormlords</a>, Lord Selwyn only agrees to a midnight meeting in a grove. The Evenstar informs Davos of his refusal to join <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Selwyn instead supports Stannis's brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> Selwyn's daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>, becomes one of Renly's <a href=\"/index.php/Rainbow_Guard\" title=\"Rainbow Guard\">Rainbow Guard</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> During the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">siege of Storm's End</a>, Renly claims he is supported by Tarth arrows.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> and Brienne discuss Selwyn.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Brienne and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> are captured by the <a href=\"/index.php/Brave_Companions\" title=\"Brave Companions\">Brave Companions</a>, and Jaime protects Brienne from rape by claiming that Selwyn will ransom her with <a href=\"/index.php/Sapphire\" title=\"Sapphire\">sapphires</a>, drawing on <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a>'s epithet of \"the Sapphire Isle\". After they are brought to <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a> sends a <a href=\"/index.php/Raven\" title=\"Raven\">raven</a> to Tarth demanding a ransom. Lord Selwyn responds by offering three hundred <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">dragons</a> for Brienne's safe return. <a href=\"/index.php/Vargo_Hoat\" title=\"Vargo Hoat\">Vargo Hoat</a> rejects the offer, however, believing Selwyn is trying to cheat him by withholding sapphires.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> ridicules Brienne and advises her to return to her father at Tarth.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)\" title=\"Elder Brother (Quiet Isle)\">Elder Brother</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Quiet_Isle\" title=\"Quiet Isle\">Quiet Isle</a> also recommends that Brienne give up her quest and return home, saying that her father would rather have a living daughter than her broken <a href=\"/index.php/Shield\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a>. Brienne tearfully explains her family's history and her life since Tarth, and that she must find <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> or die trying.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After being captured by the <a href=\"/index.php/Brotherhood_without_banners\" title=\"Brotherhood without banners\">brotherhood without banners</a>, Brienne claims that Selwyn will ransom her <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Podrick_Payne\" title=\"Podrick Payne\">Podrick Payne</a>, with sapphires, <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a>, or whatever they want.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>You are all your <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a> father claimed you were.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Brienne</b>: I never knew my mother. My father had <a href=\"/index.php/Paramour\" title=\"Paramour\">ladies</a>... a different lady every year, but...<br />\n<b>Catelyn</b>: Those were no ladies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Jaime</b>: Do you have any siblings, my lady?<br />\n</p><p><b>Brienne</b>: No. I was my father's only s—child.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Jaime</b>: Son, you meant to say. Does he think of you as a son? You make a queer sort of daughter, to be sure.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>As for you, my lady, it is said that your father is a good man. If so, I pity him. Some men are blessed with sons, some with daughters. No man deserves to be cursed with such as you.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>You have a noble father who must surely love you. Consider his grief if you should never return. Perhaps they will bring your <a href=\"/index.php/Sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sword\">sword</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Shield\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a> to him, after you have fallen. Perhaps he will even hang them in <a href=\"/index.php/Evenfall_Hall\" title=\"Evenfall Hall\">his hall</a> and look on them with pride... but if you were to ask him, I know he would tell you that he would sooner have a living daughter than a shattered shield.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)\" title=\"Elder Brother (Quiet Isle)\">Elder Brother</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A daughter. He deserves that. A daughter who could sing to him and grace <a href=\"/index.php/Evenfall_Hall\" title=\"Evenfall Hall\">his hall</a> and bear him grandsons. He deserves a son too, a strong and gallant son to bring honor to his name. <a href=\"/index.php/Galladon_Tarth\" title=\"Galladon Tarth\">Galladon</a> drowned when I was four and he was eight, though, and <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Tarth\" title=\"Alysanne Tarth\">Alysanne</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Tarth\" title=\"Arianne Tarth\">Arianne</a> died still in the cradle. I am the only child the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a> let him keep. The freakish one, not fit to be a son or daughter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a>, to the <a href=\"/index.php/Elder_Brother_(Quiet_Isle)\" title=\"Elder Brother (Quiet Isle)\">Elder Brother</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Selwyn_Tarth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span